techmeme.title: Sources: Cellebrite gave the FBI unreleased tech to access the Trump shooter's phone, a "newer Samsung model", after the FBI's first attempt to crack it failed (Bloomberg)
Google says its goo.gl URL shortener links will stop working after August 25, 2025, after it stopped generating new goo.gl URLs in March 2019 (Abner Li/9to5Google)
Austin-based Saronic, which is developing autonomous military boats, raised a $175M Series B led by a16z at a $1B+ valuation, taking its total funding to ~$245M (David Jeans/Forbes)
Netflix says its ad tier now accounts for over 45% of all signups in the markets where it's available, and ad tier memberships grew 34% QoQ in Q2 (Lucas Manfredi/The Wrap)
Peter Naylor, Netflix VP of ad sales since August 2022, is leaving, and the company will hire a head of US and Canada ad sales to fill his spot (Caitlin Huston/The Hollywood Reporter)
